Download and install XAMPP for Windows (64-bit).
Ensure proper installation and run the Apache and MySQL servers.
Open phpMyAdmin by clicking the "Admin" button under MySQL in XAMPP.
Import the alumni_db.sql file to populate the database.
Open your browser and navigate to: http://localhost/alumni/.
Explore the Alumni Management System interface.
To manage data, log in to the admin dashboard:
Username: admin
Password: admin123
Manage alumni details, job opportunities, and event notifications.
View galleries showcasing university memories.
Update or delete data based on user credentials and privileges.
Enjoy seamless alumni management and stay connected with your university community!
